## REST API

The backend exposes a RESTful API that communicates with the React frontend using JSON.

Example endpoints:

### Authentication

```
POST /api/register
POST /api/login
```

### Transactions

```
POST /api/operations
GET  /api/operations
GET  /api/monthOperations
GET  /api/allExpense
```

### Budgets

```
POST /api/budgets
GET  /api/budgets
DELETE /api/budgets/{id}
```

### Goals

```
POST /api/goals
GET  /api/goals
PUT  /api/goals/{id}
DELETE /api/goals/{id}
```

---

## Authentication

Authentication is implemented using JSON Web Tokens (JWT).

After a successful login:

1. The backend generates a JWT.
2. The frontend stores the token.
3. Every protected request includes the token inside the Authorization header.
4. The backend validates the token before processing the request.

